The Vienna Center for Logic and Algorithms of TU Wien (Vienna University of=
=0A=
Technology), calls for the nomination of authors of outstanding theses and=
=0A=
scientific works in the field of Logic and Computer Science, in the followi=
ng=0A=
two categories:=0A=
=0A=
-Outstanding Master Thesis Award*=0A=
=0A=
-Outstanding Undergraduate Thesis Award (Bachelor thesis or equivalent, 1st=
=0A=
cycle of the Bologna process)*=0A=
=0A=
*The degree must have been awarded between November 15th, 2018 and December=
=0A=
31st, 2019 (inclusive).=0A=
----------------------------------=0A=
The main areas of interest are:=0A=
----------------------------------=0A=
-Computational Logic, covering theoretical and mathematical foundations suc=
h=0A=
as proof theory, model theory, computability theory, Boolean satisfiability=
=0A=
(SAT), QBF, constraint satisfaction, satisfiability modulo theories, automa=
ted=0A=
deduction (resolution, refutation, theorem proving), non-classical logics=
=0A=
(substructural logics, multi-valued logics, deontic logics, modal and tempo=
ral=0A=
logics).=0A=
=0A=
-Algorithms and Computational Complexity, including design and analysis of=
=0A=
discrete algorithms, complexity analysis, algorithmic lower bounds,=0A=
parameterized and exact algorithms, decomposition methods, approximation=0A=
algorithms, randomized algorithms, algorithm engineering, as well as=0A=
algorithmic game theory, computational social choice, parallel algorithms,=
=0A=
graph drawing algorithms, and distributed algorithms.=0A=
=0A=
-Databases and Artificial Intelligence, concerned with logical methods for=
=0A=
modeling, storing, and drawing inferences from data and knowledge. This=0A=
includes subjects like query languages based on logical concepts (Datalog,=
=0A=
variants of SQL, XML, and SPARQL), novel database-theoretical methods (sche=
ma=0A=
mappings, information extraction and integration), logic programming,=0A=
knowledge representation and reasoning (ontologies, answer-set programming,=
=0A=
belief change, inconsistency handling, argumentation, planning).=0A=
=0A=
-Verification, concerned with logical methods and automated tools for=0A=
reasoning about the behavior and correctness of complex state-based systems=
=0A=
such as software and hardware designs as well as hybrid systems. This range=
s=0A=
from model checking, program analysis and abstraction to new interdisciplin=
ary=0A=
areas such as fault localization, program repair, program synthesis, and th=
e=0A=
analysis of biological systems.=0A=
=0A=
-Formal Methods for Security and Privacy, covering design and analysis=0A=
techniques for security and privacy critical systems, such as cryptographic=
=0A=
protocols, software, hardware and so on. The category of formal methods is =
to=0A=
be meant in a broad sense, including related questions in logic, model=0A=
checking, static analysis, dynamic monitoring, theorem proving, and artific=
ial=0A=
intelligence.=0A=
=0A=
----------------------------------=0A=
Awards=0A=
----------------------------------=0A=
-The Outstanding Master Thesis Award:  1200 EUR=0A=
-The Outstanding Undergraduate Thesis Award: 800 EUR=0A=
-The winners will be invited to present their work at an award ceremony in=
=0A=
Vienna.=0A=
=0A=
----------------------------------=0A=
Eligibility=0A=
----------------------------------=0A=
-The degree must have been awarded between November 15th, 2018 and December=
=0A=
31st, 2019 (inclusive).=0A=
-Students who obtained their degree at TU Wien are not eligible.=0A=
=0A=
----------------------------------=0A=
Nomination Requirements=0A=
----------------------------------=0A=
Nominations must include:=0A=
=0A=
-A cover page that contains the name and contact details of the nominated=
=0A=
person, the title of the work for which the person is being nominated, awar=
d=0A=
category, the date on which the degree was awarded, and the name of the=0A=
university=0A=
=0A=
-An English summary of the thesis of maximum 3 pages, excluding references =
(A4=0A=
or letter page size, 11pt font min). The summary must clearly state the mai=
n=0A=
contribution of the work, its novelty, and its relevance to some of the=0A=
aforementioned areas of interest=0A=
=0A=
-The CV of the nominated person, including publication list (if applicable=
=0A=
=0A=
-An endorsement letter from a supervisor or another proposing person. The=
=0A=
letter must clearly state the independent and novel contribution of the=0A=
student, and why the proposer believes the student deserves the award. The=
=0A=
endorsement letter may be provided after the submission deadline, and email=
ed=0A=
directly to award (AT) logic-cs.at.=0A=
=0A=
-The full thesis=0A=
=0A=
All documents should be in English, with the exception of the thesis. In ca=
se=0A=
the thesis is in a different language, it must be accompanied by a research=
=0A=
report in English of at least 10 pages that should be sufficient for the=0A=
committee to evaluate the merit and quality of the submitted work.=0A=
=0A=
  ----------------------------------=0A=
Instructions for submitting nominations=0A=
----------------------------------=0A=
-Nominations should be submitted electronically using the following link to=
=0A=
EasyChair here=0A=
-Submissions consist of two pdf files. The first is a single pdf file=0A=
containing all documents for the nomination except the full thesis; the=0A=
documents should appear in the order they are listed above. The second pdf=
=0A=
file is the full thesis=0A=
-The endorsement letter may optionally be sent by email by the endorser and=
=0A=
omitted from the Easychair submission. In this case, please email the lette=
r=0A=
as a pdf file, including the name of the nominated person in the subject, t=
o=0A=
award (AT) logic-cs DOT at=0A=
-The submission must be accompanied by a plain text electronic abstract of =
the=0A=
thesis of at most 400 words, and three keywords.=0A=
-The nominated student must be listed as the first and corresponding author=
  in=0A=
the submission form.=0A=
